'''Guus Berend Til''' (born 22 December 1997) is a Dutch professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as an [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Eredivisie]] club [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].<ref name="soccerway">{{Soccerway|guus-til/451981}}</ref>

==Early life==
Til was born in [[Samfya]], Zambia, where his father worked in the development field. He moved to the Netherlands at age 3, as his family settled in the [[Bijlmermeer]] neighbourhood of [[Amsterdam]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Guus Til (AZ): 'Ik was enige blanke die kon voetballen' |url=https://www.ewmagazine.nl/nederland/achtergrond/2018/04/606865-606865/ |website=EWmagazine.nl |access-date=20 May 2022 |language=nl |date=18 April 2018}}</ref>

==Club career==
===AZ===
Til is a youth exponent from [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]]. He made his professional debut on 4 August 2016 as a substitute in a [[UEFA Europa League]] play-off match against [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]], replacing [[Joris van Overeem]] after 71 minutes.<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/08/04/europe/uefa-cup/pas-giannina/stichting-az/2282887/|title=PAS Giannina vs. AZ - 4 August 2016 - Soccerway|publisher=soccerway.com|accessdate=24 August 2016}}</ref>

===Spartak Moscow===
On 5 August 2019, [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]] announced they had signed Guus Til from [[AZ Alkmaar|AZ]] for a reported transfer fee of €18 million (the third highest transfer fee in club history at the time). He also signed a four-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Гус Тиль стал игроком Спартака |url=https://spartak.com/news/2019-08-05-gus_til_stal_igrokom_spartaka/ |publisher=FC Spartak Moscow |accessdate=5 August 2019 |language=Russian |date=5 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Spartak Transfer Maakt Til Derde Topverkoop AZ In Vier Jaar |url=https://www.vtbl.nl/nieuws/artikel/4804501/spartak-transfer-maakt-til-derde-topverkoop-az-vier-jaar |website=www.vtbl.nl |date=5 August 2019 |accessdate=5 August 2019 |archive-date=5 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190805182246/https://www.vtbl.nl/nieuws/artikel/4804501/spartak-transfer-maakt-til-derde-topverkoop-az-vier-jaar |url-status=dead }}</ref> In his [[Russian Premier League]] debut on 11 August 2019 against [[FC Akhmat Grozny|Akhmat Grozny]], he provided 2 assists in a 3–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Russian Premier League]]|url=https://eng.premierliga.ru/match/match_13154.html|title=Akhmat v Spartak game report|date=11 August 2019}}</ref> He scored his first goal for Spartak on 25 August 2019 in an away game against [[PFC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov Samara]], when his added-time goal gave his team a 2–1 comeback away victory.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Russian Premier League]]|url=https://eng.premierliga.ru/match/match_13172.html|title=Krylia Sovetov v Spartak game report|date=25 August 2019}}</ref>

====Loan to SC Freiburg====
On 3 September 2020, Til joined [[Bundesliga]] side [[SC Freiburg]] on a season-long loan with option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[Russian Premier League]]|url=https://www.scfreiburg.com/node/54819|title=Guus Til kommt von Spartak Moskau|trans-title=Guus Til arrives from Spartak Moscow|date=3 September 2020|language=German|access-date=3 September 2020|archive-date=3 September 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200903172225/https://www.scfreiburg.com/node/54819|url-status=dead}}</ref>

====Loan to Feyenoord====
On 2 June 2021, Til extended his contract with Spartak until 31 May 2024 and was loaned to [[Feyenoord]] for the 2021–22 season. Spartak held an option to terminate his loan early if he appeared in fewer than half of all official games for Feyenoord up until 1 January 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Spartak Moscow]]|url=https://spartak.com/news/2021-06-02-til_prodlil_kontrakt_so_spartakom_i_arendovan_feyyenoordom/|title=Тиль продлил контракт со "Спартаком" и арендован "Фейеноордом"|date=2 June 2021|language=ru}}</ref>

On 29 July 2021, Til scored a hat-trick against [[FC Drita]] of Kosovo in the second qualifying round for the inaugural edition of the [[2021–22 UEFA Europa Conference League|UEFA Europa Conference League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaconferenceleague/match/2032895/|title=Feyenoord 3-2 Drita|website=UEFA|date=29 July 2021|access-date=3 October 2021}}</ref>

On 3 October, Til was named the Eredivisie Player of the Month for September following four goals in three league matches for Feyenoord, which all ended in victory for the Rotterdam club.<ref name=EPOM />

===PSV Eindhoven===
On 4 July 2022, Til signed a four-year contract with [[PSV Eindhoven|PSV]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=PSV|url=https://www.psv.nl/nieuwspagina/artikel/definitief-psv-neemt-guus-til-over-van-spartak-moskou.htm|title=PSV NEEMT GUUS TIL OVER VAN SPARTAK MOSKOU|date=4 July 2022|access-date=4 July 2022|language=nl}}</ref> Til scored a hat-trick on his debut for the club, a 5–3 win over rivals [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] in the [[2022 Johan Cruyff Shield|Johan Cruyff Shield]] on 30 July.<ref name=JCSwin>{{cite web|url=https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/matches/match/ajax-psv-30-07-2022.htm|title=Ajax - PSV|website=PSV.nl|date=30 July 2022|accessdate=30 July 2022|archive-date=23 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220923024833/https://www.psv.nl/english-psv/matches/match/ajax-psv-30-07-2022.htm|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==International career==
Til was a youth international for the Netherlands.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/19/57e32d1e-aea21781-624482 |title=Speler: Guus Til &#124; OnsOranje |access-date=6 March 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170306212645/http://www.onsoranje.nl/team-statistieken/teams/speler/19/57e32d1e-aea21781-624482 |archive-date=6 March 2017 |url-status=dead }}</ref>

In March 2018, Til earned from [[Ronald Koeman]] his debut international call-up to the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/5166179/weghorst-plek-in-voorselectie-oranje-stap-allergrootste-droom.html|title = Weghorst: 'Plek in voorselectie Oranje stap naar allergrootste droom'|date = 7 March 2018}}</ref> He made his debut coming on as a substitute for [[Kenny Tete]] in the 78th minute of a 3–0 friendly win against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] on 26 March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=499991|title=Portugal v Netherlands game report|date=26 March 2018}}</ref>

In May 2021, the [[Football Association of Zambia]] had confirmed they had contacted Til over a possible switch of international allegiance. Zambia head coach [[Milutin Sredojević]] stated that Til was still undecided on his future.<ref>{{Cite web|date=2021-05-27|title=Milutin Sredojevic confirms Zambia's approach for Dutch midfielder Guus Til|url=https://www.kickoff.com/news/articles/world-news/categories/news/african-football/milutin-sredojevic-confirms-zambia-s-approach-for-dutch-midfielder-guus-til/699857?gallery=667713&gallery-page=10|access-date=2021-05-28|website=Kick Off}}</ref> Til returned to the Netherlands national team in September 2021 scoring his first goal in a 6–1 win over [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rijnmond.nl/nieuws/1373531/Bijlow-en-doelpuntenmaker-Til-walsen-met-Oranje-over-Kokcu-en-Turkije-heen-in-WK-kwalificatieduel |title= Bijlow en doelpuntenmaker Til walsen met Oranje over Kökcü en Turkije heen in WK-kwalificatieduel |language=Dutch |date=7 September 2021 |access-date=7 September 2021}}</ref>

